OL,3,CThousands of bar staff to be trained
OL,4,Cto deal with spiking incidents
OL,6,FChief Constable Lucy D'Orsi of British
OL,7,FTransport Police will highlight the
OL,8,Frelaunch of the text-to-report number,
OL,9,F61016, which is now free across all
OL,10,Fmajor networks and invites women to
OL,11,Fcontact the force for help in the
OL,12,Fevent of harassment on the train.
OL,14,FOther figures attending the meeting
OL,15,Finclude Kate Nicholls, chief executive
OL,16,Fof UKHospitality and chairwoman of the
OL,17,FInstitute of Licensing, and Chief
OL,18,FConstable Maggie Blythe, the National
OL,19,FPolice Chiefs' Council lead for VAWG.
